    "This transparency enables practitioners to verify backdoor removal and diagnose failures early-a critical requirement for deploying defenses in safety-critical systems.Future Work: Testing on ResNet-18 architecture would provide fair comparison with SOTA.",
    "We hypothesize our method could achieve ∼88-90% clean accuracy with ResNet-18 while maintaining low ASR and XAI benefits.",
    "Value of XAI in SecurityIntegration of Grad-CAM provides multiple benefits: Transparency: Practitioners can visually verify backdoor removal by observing heatmap evolution.Early Diagnosis: If heatmaps don't show expected attention shift by epochs 5-7, practitioners can terminate and adjust hyperparameters early.Quantitative Validation: TAR complements traditional accuracy metrics, providing trigger-specific measurement that directly assesses backdoor influence.",
    "C. Limitations and Future WorkLimited Experimental Scope: Current evaluation uses CIFAR-10 with a custom CNN architecture.",
    "Future work should validate on: (i) standard architectures (ResNet-18/50) for fair SOTA comparison, (ii) larger datasets (CIFAR-100, ImageNet), (iii) diverse trigger types (blended, semantic, invisible).Single Trigger Assumption: Our experiments focus on one trigger pattern (4×4 white square)."
